file.name: openapi.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0

info:
  title: Kafka Streams User Report microservice
  version: 1.0.0
  description: |-
    # Kafka Streams User Report Service
servers:
  - url: https://kafka.networknt.com

paths:
  /report:
    get:
      operationId: reportUsers
      summary: Generate a report based on user contry 
      responses:
        '200':
          description: Successful response
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: 
                type: array
                items: 
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/CountryUserCount'
        '400':
          description: Unexpected error
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Status"
      security:
        - user_auth:
            - user:r  
components:
  securitySchemes:
    user_auth:
      type: oauth2
      description: This API uses OAuth 2.0 with the client credential grant flow.
      flows:
        clientCredentials:
          tokenUrl: 'https://localhost:6882/token'
          scopes:
            user:w: user write
            user:r: user read
  schemas:
    Status:
      type: object
      properties:
        statusCode: 
          description: HTTP response code
          type: integer
        code:
          description: Code is the machine-readable error code
          type: string
        message:
          description: Error messsage
          type: string
        description: 
          description: The detailed description of the error status  
          type: string
      required:
      - statusCode
      - code
    CountryUserCount:
      type: object
      properties:
        country: 
          description: User Country
          type: string
        count:
          description: Number of Users
          type: integer
      required:
      - country
      - count
